  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nUsers should be able to fetch the keystore and truststore passwords from different types of Vaults via `CredentialsProvider`:\r\n\r\nhttps://quarkus.io/guides/credentials-provider\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nCheck `CredentialsProvider` in the `Vertx HTTP` recorder if no keystore/truststore passwords are configured.\r\nThe problem there is that `password` is a default - we can still default to `password` if neither the password is explicitly configured nor `CredentialsProvider` is available. Also, dropping `password` as a default value can only really break the tests as no one will ever use such a default value in production, so may be we can just go ahead and remove it. ",
